# Documentation policy

Read and follow [`docs/DOCUMENTATION.md`](../docs/DOCUMENTATION.md) before editing any user-facing markdown.

## Quick rules

- **`README.md`** — front door only: what/why, quick start, funnel summary, privacy defaults, doc map. Max ~120 lines.
- **`SETUP.md`** — install, hooks, per-IDE behavior, CLI flags, doctor.
- **`docs/API.md`** — MCP tool reference (update when adding tools).
- **`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — funnel layers, storage, widening vs HITL.
- **`docs/TELEMETRY.md`** — schema, KPIs, opt-in/out (README keeps defaults table only).
- **`docs/DEV.md`** — tests, security gates, bench SLAs.
- **`CLAUDE.md`** — contributor stack and conventions.

Do **not** duplicate long tables across files. Link instead.

When adding an MCP tool: `src/mcp/index.ts` + `tests/contract/` + `docs/API.md`.

`ROADMAP*.md` is gitignored — planning docs stay local; never link from README or other committed docs.
